	<h1>Birth certificate</h1>
	<form>

		<div class="info">
		<p>A Birth Certificate is a vital record that establishes the birth of a child. It is an official form that gives details on the time and place of a person's birth, and his or her name, sex, mother's name and (usually) father's name. The word "birth certificate" can refer to either the original document or a certified true copy of or representation of the original record of birth document. Birth Certificate Valid Forever. Birth Certificate can be used as proof of identity to get Driver Licence, Passport, etc.</p>

		<h2>Required Documents</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Valid Identity document.</li>
            <li>Driving license</li>
            <li>Passport</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Required Information</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Name of the applicant and address</li>
            <li>Full name of the person named on the certificate</li>
            <li>Fathers and Mothers Full name</li>
            <li>Sex </li>
            <li>No. Copies required</li>
            <li>Date of Birth</li>
            <li>Registrars Division</li>
            <li>Number and Date of Registration entry (if known)</li>
            <li>Period of search desired </li>
		</ul>

